AKURE – Children numbering over 50 have been allegedly discovered and rescued from an underground compartment in a church building at Valentino Area of Ondo city, Ondo State on Friday night. They were rescued by the police from Ondo area command, while the pastor and a number of members of the church were also arrested. A minute, 40-seconds video clip showing the faces of some of the children with some voices on the background disclosed that the vehicle in which the children were was a police van. One of the voices video on the background in the video clip, which had gone viral on social media, revealed that “These are kidnapped children found in the underground cell of a church in Valentino Area of Ondo . The pastor and some members of the church have been arrested and were also in the patrol van of the police.” Confirming the incident, spokesman for the state Police Command, Mrs. Funmilayo Odunlami, an Superintendent of Police(SP) disclosed the victims had been taken to the headquarters of the state command at Alagbaka, Akure, the state capital. She said: “I don’t have the details yet but they are bringing the victims to the headquarters. I will give you the details as soon as I get it from the DPO.”